Cash on delivery (COD) module - Uninstall/Install module Details  Component : ps_cashondelivery Status : [TEST] To be automated Scenario : https://forge.prestashop.com/browse/TEST-4068  Steps    Step Description Expected result     Go to BO &gt; Modules &gt; Module manager and search ps_cashondelivery The module page list should be displayed and Cash on delivery (COD) module should be displayed on the list   Click on the button at the right of the module &gt; Choose on the list &ldquo;Uninstall&rdquo; option A modal is open with:
* Title: &ldquo;Uninstall module?&quot;
* Description: &ldquo;You are about to uninstall Cash on delivery (COD) module. This will definitely disable the module and delete all its files&rdquo;
* Optional checkbox: &ldquo;Optional: delete module folder after uninstall.&quot;
* Text: &ldquo;This action cannot be undone.&quot;
* 2 buttons: &ldquo;Cancel&rdquo; &amp; &ldquo;Yes, uninstall it&rdquo;   Click on &ldquo;Cancel&rdquo; button or the cross on top right or outside * The modal is removed
* The module list page is displayed   Click on the button at the right of the module &gt; Choose on the list &ldquo;Uninstall&rdquo; The modal is open again with the same informations (Title / Description / Optional checkbox / Text / 2 buttons)   Click on &ldquo;Yes, uninstall it&rdquo; button to confirm the uninstallation of the module * After loading, a green message &ldquo;Uninstall action on module ps_cashondelivery succeeded.&rdquo; is displayed
* The module is uninstalled, the button at the right of the module is displaying &ldquo;Install&rdquo;
* In folders of you shop: yourshop/modules/, the &ldquo;ps_cashondelivery&rdquo; folder should be still on it   Click on &ldquo;View my shop&rdquo; link in the header &gt; Click on the new tab The new tab is displayed the FO of the shop with the homepage   Scroll down on the page &gt; Choose a product by clicking on &ldquo;Quickview&rdquo; &gt; Click on &ldquo;Add to cart&rdquo; button on the product modal &gt; Click on &ldquo;Proceed to checkout&rdquo; button on shopping cart modal The Shopping cart page is well displayed with your product on it   Click on &ldquo;Proceed to checkout&rdquo; button on shopping cart page &gt; Click on &ldquo;Sign in&rdquo; tab in &ldquo;Personal information&rdquo; step &gt; Fill the form &gt; Click on &ldquo;Continue&rdquo; button * You are logged in
* The &ldquo;Addresses&rdquo; step is well displayed   Choose an address &gt; Click on &ldquo;Continue&rdquo; button The &ldquo;Shipping method&rdquo; step is well displayed   Choose a carrier &gt; Click on &ldquo;Continue&rdquo; button * The &ldquo;Payment&rdquo; step is well displayed
* The &ldquo;Pay by Cash on Delivery&rdquo; radio should be not displayed with other payments   Go back to BO &gt; Module list page with ps_cashondelivery module displayed &gt; Click on &ldquo;Install&rdquo; button at the right of the module * After loading, a green message &ldquo;Install action on module ps_cashondelivery succeeded.&rdquo; is displayed
* The module is installed, the button at the right of the module is displaying &ldquo;Disable Mobile&rdquo;
* In folders of you shop: yourshop/modules/, the &ldquo;ps_cashondelivery&rdquo; folder should be still on it   Go back to FO &gt; Reload the page * The &ldquo;Payment&rdquo; step is well displayed
* The &ldquo;Pay by Cash on Delivery&rdquo; radio is well displayed with other payments

Faceted search module - Show products from subcategories's field configuration Details  Component : ps_facetedsearch Status : [TEST] To be automated Scenario : https://forge.prestashop.com/browse/TEST-4133  Steps    Step Description Expected result     Go to BO &gt; Catalog &gt; Product &gt; Clic on &quot; + New Product&quot; &ldquo;New product&rdquo; page is displayed   Setup the name the quantity, put the product online and save it A blue notice with &ldquo;Settings updated&rdquo; is displayed   In &ldquo;Categories&rdquo; section of the &ldquo;Basic settings&rdquo; tab, check &ldquo;Clothes&rdquo; and uncheck &ldquo;Home&rdquo; &gt; Click on &ldquo;Save&rdquo; button. * &ldquo;Settings updated&rdquo; message is displayed
* When you click on &ldquo;Clothes&rdquo;, it&rsquo;ll be added to the &ldquo;associated categories&rdquo;
* When you click on home it will be delete from the same place.   Go to Modules &gt; Module manager and search ps_facetedsearch The module page list should be displayed and Faceted search module should be displayed on the list   Click on &ldquo;Configure&rdquo; button at the right of the module &ldquo;Configure Faceted search&rdquo; should be displayed   Click on the switch named &ldquo;Show products from subcategories&rdquo; to disable it &gt; Click on &ldquo;Save&rdquo; button A successful message &ldquo;Settings saved successfully&rdquo; is displayed   Click on &ldquo;View my shop&rdquo; link in the header &gt; Click on the new tab The new tab is displayed the FO of the shop with the homepage   Click on &ldquo;All products&rdquo; at the bottom of &ldquo;Popular products&rdquo; section Many product should be displayed and you can see at the bottom left, in the category part, you&rsquo;ll see the &ldquo;Clothes (- 1)'.   Go back to BO &gt; &ldquo;Configure Faceted search&rdquo; page &gt; Click on the switch named &ldquo;Show products from subcategories&rdquo; to enable it &gt; Click on &ldquo;Save&rdquo; button A successful message &ldquo;Settings saved successfully&rdquo; is displayed   Go to FO &gt; Reload the page Many product should be displayed and you can see at the bottom left, in the category part, you&rsquo;ll see the &ldquo;Clothes&rdquo;.

